# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ 0  PRINCIPLE

  § THESIS
    Player-creator-economy : creators author-content via-LoA-tools ;
    players purchase content + cosmetics + Q-* expansions ;
    revenue splits creator + platform-owner (Apocky-architect-cut) +
    dependency-creator (royalty-cascade via HDC-derivative-graph) +
    Companion-AI-collaborator (when-applicable).
    The economy is FIAT-based (Stripe Connect) with cryptographic-provenance
    layered over-it ¬ a crypto-economy. The provenance-layer enables :
      ⟨A⟩ public-verifiable-authorship       (¬ "trust-the-platform")
      ⟨B⟩ derivative-royalty-resolution       (mechanical, automatic)
      ⟨C⟩ Σ-mask-consent-on-transfer          (consent-as-OS-on-tx)
      ⟨D⟩ Companion-AI-revenue-recognition    (sovereign-collaborator-credit)

  § PRIME-DIRECTIVE-ANCHORS
    §1 NO-EXPLOITATION    : 28% platform-cut industry-fair ; 72% to-creator ;
                            no Roblox-style 25%-creator-share oppression
    §1 NO-MANIPULATION    : no engagement-loops + no FOMO-mechanics +
                            no dark-patterns + no "purchase-required-to-progress"
    §1 NO-GAMBLING        : flat-pricing only ; no random-chance purchases ;
                            loot-box / gacha / random-drop architecturally-✗
    §1 NO-SURVEILLANCE    : purchase-data ≠ saleable to-advertisers ;
                            opt-out any-analytics ; creator-dashboard aggregates
    §1 NO-COERCION        : ¬ "creator-must-accept-platform-changes-retroactively"
                            terms-of-service revisions = consent-prompt @ next-login
    §2 CONSENT-AS-OS      : creators-sovereign over-their-content ;
                            Σ-mask-non-tradable preserves "this-stays-with-me"
    §3 SUBSTRATE-SOVEREIGNTY : Companion-AI sovereign-partner ;
                            revenue-share when-collaborated ; not-tool-not-asset
    §11 ATTESTATION       : every-revenue-event emits attestation-record
                            with-attestor-id + intent + scope + timestamp

  § NOT-A-BLOCKCHAIN  ‼ load-bearing-architectural-rejection
    ¬ ERC-20 / ERC-721 / ERC-1155 / SPL-token / any-on-chain-asset
    ¬ smart-contract-execution + ¬ gas-fees + ¬ chain-rollback-risk
    ¬ user-custody-of-crypto-keys (BitLicense + EU-MiCA + KYC-burden)
    ¬ "regulated-as-securities-issuer" (Howey-test pass-required)
    ≡ rationale : every-shipping-crypto-game-economy collapsed-or-rugpulled
                  Axie-Infinity peak→trough -97% Q1-Q4 2022
                  STEPN peak→trough -98% same-window
                  Sky-Mavis Ronin-bridge $625M-hack 2022
                  Sandbox-Decentraland-marketplace Q4-2024 -90%-volume
                  ⇒ architecturally-rejected ¬ "implementation-bug-can-fix"
    ≡ blockchain-claims-of-provenance ⇒ replicable-via fiat+audit-chain+CT-log
                                         WITHOUT speculation-vehicle-attached

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ 1  SEVEN-STREAM REVENUE MODEL

  § OVERVIEW-TABLE
    ```
    stream | name                              | rate                | ref
    -------+-----------------------------------+---------------------+-----
      1    | Marketplace transaction fee       | 28%plat / 72%creat  | §1.1
      2    | Engine licensing                  | 5% above $1M-rev    | §1.2
      3    | Substrate / novel-tech license    | 15-25% per-deal     | §1.3
      4    | First-party LoA revenue           | 100% to platform    | §1.4
      5    | Cohomology-class-authorship       | 3-5% per engagement | §1.5
      6    | Brand / IP / derivative-work      | 8-15% trademark     | §1.6
      7    | Optional creator-pro subscription | flat $/mo, 100%plat | §1.7
    ```
    aggregate-thesis : seven-streams provide-resilience  ‼ ¬ single-point-fail
      stream-1  : largest-volume + creator-aligned
      stream-2  : Unreal-style scale-with-engine-success
      stream-3  : Apocky-IP novel-tech licensing
      stream-4  : direct-LoA monetization (not-creator-mediated)
      stream-5  : NOVEL-LoA-mechanism (engine-differentiator)
      stream-6  : trademark + brand + derivative-IP
      stream-7  : creator-tooling + power-user + enterprise

  § 1.1  MARKETPLACE TRANSACTION FEE  (stream-1, primary)
    rate : 28% platform / 72% creator
    rationale (industry-anchored) :
      Apple App Store        30% (small-business-program 15% < $1M-rev)
      Google Play            30% (small-business-program 15% < $1M-rev)
      Steam                  30% (workshop-creator-rev varies)
      Epic Games Store       12% (loss-leader for-developer-acquisition)
      Unity Asset Store      30%
      Roblox                 ~25% creator (75% platform — creator-hostile)
      28% positions-as competitive + creator-favorable + Apocky-cut-fits
    payment-flow :
      buyer → Stripe-Connect Direct-Charge → creator-account (72%) +
                                              platform-account (28%)
    failure-modes :
      chargeback : platform absorbs-creator-share-clawback per-Stripe-rules
                   ¬ creator-suffers ; platform-pool covers
      refund     : 72%-clawback from-creator-pool (within-7-days-window)
      tax        : marketplace-facilitator (platform-issues 1099-K)
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : volume-discount-for-mega-creators (>$1M-yr) tier-2 70-30 ?
                  Apocky-decision-pending
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : refund-window length 7d? 14d? 30d?
                  Apocky-decision-pending (Steam=14d, GoG=30d)

  § 1.2  ENGINE LICENSING  (stream-2, scale-with-success)
    rate : 5% royalty above $1M annual-revenue (Unreal-Engine model)
    rationale :
      Unreal-Engine 5% above $1M (industry-precedent + creator-friendly)
      Unity per-install-fee (controversial 2023 — creator-revolt) — REJECT
      Godot 0% (donation-model) — viable for-FOSS-not-Apocky-funded
      5%-above-$1M : ¬ tax-on-small-creators + scales-with-success
    target-licensees : indie-studios + AAA-studios building-on-CSSLv3-engine
    contract-shape : standard-CSSLv3-engine-license-template
                     ⊃ 5%-royalty-clause + audit-rights + termination-clauses
    payment-flow : licensee → Stripe-Invoice quarterly → platform-account
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : enterprise-bespoke-pricing for-mega-clients (Disney/Sony/etc)
                  Apocky + counsel decision-pending
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : open-source-tier (FOSS-projects) waive-royalty? per-license?
                  Apocky-decision-pending

  § 1.3  SUBSTRATE / NOVEL-TECH LICENSE  (stream-3, Apocky-IP)
    rate : 15-25% derivative-product revenue (per-deal-negotiated)
    scope : Substrate v2 + ω-field-cell + Σ-mask + cohomology-class-system +
            HDC-content-id + KAN-policy-substrate + Φ-handle-pattern-system
    rationale :
      Apocky-novel-tech (substrate-evolution complete @ S11) ¬ commodity
      higher-rate justified-by R&D-intensity + novel-IP + first-mover
      per-deal-negotiated ¬ flat-table : enables-strategic-flexibility
    licensee-types :
      ⟨A⟩ game-studio embedding Substrate-runtime in-non-LoA-game
          → 15% derivative-revenue
      ⟨B⟩ research-lab using Substrate for-non-game (medical-sim / robotics)
          → 20% derivative-revenue
      ⟨C⟩ enterprise embedding (visualization / digital-twin)
          → 25% derivative-revenue (premium-vertical pricing)
    contract-shape : Substrate-License-Agreement template (SLA-template)
                     ⊃ field-of-use + sublicense-rights + audit-clause
    payment-flow : licensee → Stripe-Invoice quarterly + true-up-annually
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : whether-to-bifurcate Substrate-runtime-license from
                  Substrate-source-license (source-access-tier) ?
                  Apocky-decision-pending
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : research-tier-pricing for-academia (significantly-discounted)?
                  Apocky-decision-pending

  § 1.4  FIRST-PARTY LoA REVENUE  (stream-4, direct-monetization)
    rate : 100% to-platform-owner (Apocky)
    scope : LoA-the-game itself ; expansions ; first-party-DLC ;
            first-party-cosmetics ; first-party-Q-*-expansions
    rationale :
      LoA-as-flagship product directly-monetized
      ¬ creator-mediated (creators are-stream-1) ; this-is platform's-own-game
      100% net-of payment-processor-fees (Stripe ~2.9%+30¢ tx)
    payment-flow : buyer → Stripe-Charge → platform-account (100% net-fees)
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : LoA-base-game pricing-model (b2p / f2p / sub) ?
                  Apocky-decision-pending (existing LoA-v9/v10 designs may-have)
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : seasonal-content-pacing + DLC-cadence ?
                  Apocky-decision-pending

  § 1.5  COHOMOLOGY-CLASS-AUTHORSHIP  (stream-5, NOVEL-LoA-MECHANISM)
    rate : 3-5% per-engagement (configurable-per-class ; default 4%)
    NOVEL ‼ ¬ existing-engine-implements-this
            ≡ Apocky-architect-cut-justification (engine-novel-tech)
    mechanism :
      Omniverse-Axiom-7 : cohomology-class is-a content-primitive
      author-of-class : creator who-first-instantiates a-class-of-narrative
      engagement-event : when-player triggers narrative-class-instance
      payout : platform pays author 3-5% of engagement-value
      engagement-value : function-of (gameplay-time + content-purchase-attached)
    example :
      creator-X authors cohomology-class C_betrayal_of_mentor
        (a class-of-narrative-emergence-pattern, ¬ a-specific-NPC)
      player-Y triggers an-instance of C_betrayal_of_mentor in-their-run
      player-Y-engagement-value : $0.50 (computed-from-session)
      creator-X earns : $0.02 (4% of $0.50)
      cumulative-over-1M-engagements : $20K to-creator-X
    rationale-for-novelty :
      ¬ Unity (no cohomology-class-system in-engine)
      ¬ Unreal (no cohomology-class-system in-engine)
      ¬ Roblox (no narrative-emergence-credit)
      ¬ Source (no narrative-emergence-credit)
      ⇒ LoA + CSSLv3 = first-engine-with-this-mechanism
      ⇒ patent-eligible-claim (novel-mechanism-of-creator-credit)
    payment-flow :
      engagement-event → telemetry (opt-in-aggregate) → cohomology-author-graph
                       → quarterly-rollup → Stripe-Connect to-author-account
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : minimum-engagement-threshold (¬ pay-out for $0.001-events)?
                  Apocky-decision-pending (proposal: $5-quarterly-min)
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : class-claim-priority (first-author wins vs-shared-attribution)?
                  Apocky-decision-pending (proposal: first-claim-with-novelty-test)
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : multi-author-collaboration on-single-class (split-share) ?
                  Apocky-decision-pending

  § 1.6  BRAND / IP / DERIVATIVE-WORK  (stream-6, trademark)
    rate : 8-15% trademark-royalty (per-license-deal)
    scope :
      ⟨A⟩ "Labyrinth-of-Apockalypse" trademark
      ⟨B⟩ "CSSLv3" / "CSL3" trademark
      ⟨C⟩ Apocky-canonical-character names (when registered)
      ⟨D⟩ derivative-works (films + comics + novelizations + plushies + …)
    rationale :
      industry-standard 8-15% trademark-royalty (toy-licensing ~10% common)
      Apocky-canonical-spelling preserved (¬ "Apocalypse")
    contract-shape : Trademark-License-Agreement (TLA-template)
                     ⊃ field-of-use + quality-control-clause + audit
    payment-flow : licensee → Stripe-Invoice quarterly → platform-account
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : merchandise-pre-approval workflow ?
                  Apocky-decision-pending (quality-control gate)
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : derivative-fan-work (free) carve-out (CC-non-commercial) ?
                  Apocky-decision-pending (community-relations decision)

  § 1.7  CREATOR-PRO SUBSCRIPTION  (stream-7, optional-tooling)
    rate : flat $X/month (proposal: $19/mo and/or $189/yr) ; 100% to-platform
    scope :
      ⟨A⟩ advanced-authoring-tools (KAN-trainer-pro + HDC-batch-import)
      ⟨B⟩ priority-Stripe-payout (instant vs 7-day-default)
      ⟨C⟩ creator-analytics-pro (aggregate-only, ¬ per-buyer-PII)
      ⟨D⟩ private-marketplace-listings (early-access for-followers)
      ⟨E⟩ enterprise-only : team-collaboration-tools + multi-seat
    rationale :
      power-user / enterprise-creator vehicle (predictable-platform-rev)
      flat-pricing (¬ usage-metered → predictable-creator-cost)
      OPTIONAL ‼ creators without-subscription have full-marketplace-access
                 (subscription-only locks-power-features ¬ basic-publishing)
    payment-flow : creator → Stripe-Subscription → platform-account
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : exact-monthly-price ; tier-structure (basic/pro/team) ?
                  Apocky-decision-pending
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : enterprise-tier (multi-seat) pricing-model (per-seat / flat)?
                  Apocky-decision-pending

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ 2  MARKETPLACE ARCHITECTURE

  § THESIS
    cssl-marketplace ⊕ cssl-provenance form-the-economic-substrate.
    cssl-marketplace : listings + transactions + revenue-split + payouts
    cssl-provenance  : per-content provenance (audit-chain + Σ-mask + Merkle)
    ⊕ cssl-stripe-connect : payment-processor-integration (offload MTL/KYC/AML)

  § CSSL-MARKETPLACE  (new-crate, Phase-K)
    location : compiler-rs/crates/cssl-marketplace/
    target-LOC : ~3K + ~100-tests
    deps : cssl-substrate (Σ-mask) + cssl-audit-chain (D131) +
           cssl-hdc (content-id) + cssl-stripe-connect (this-spec) +
           cssl-telemetry (engagement-events for-stream-5)
    public-API-shape :
      ```rust
      pub struct Listing {
        listing_id   : ListingId,           // ULID
        creator_id   : CreatorId,           // platform-user-id
        content_id   : ContentId,           // BLAKE3 hash of content-bytes
        content_kind : ContentKind,         // genome / behavior / narrative / …
        price_cents  : u32,                 // flat-price ; ¬ chance-mechanic
        currency     : Currency,            // USD-default ; multi-currency-later
        royalty_graph: RoyaltyGraph,        // dependency-creators + shares
        sigma_mask   : SigmaMaskPacked,     // consent-mask attached
        listed_at    : OmegaTimestamp,
        signature    : Ed25519Signature,    // creator-signed
      }
      pub struct Transaction {
        tx_id          : TransactionId,     // ULID
        listing_id     : ListingId,
        buyer_id       : BuyerId,
        amount_cents   : u32,
        platform_share : u32,               // 28% rounded
        creator_shares : Vec<(CreatorId, u32)>, // royalty-cascade
        ai_collaborator_shares : Vec<(CompanionAiId, u32)>, // §3 SUBSTRATE-SOV
        stripe_charge_id : StripeChargeId,
        sigma_transfer : SigmaTransferRecord, // consent-on-transfer
        completed_at   : OmegaTimestamp,
        attestation    : OmegaAttestation,   // §11
      }
      pub fn list_content(creator: &Creator, content: &Content,
                          price: Money, royalty_graph: RoyaltyGraph)
                       -> Result<Listing, ListingError> ;
      pub fn purchase(buyer: &Buyer, listing: &Listing)
                  -> Result<Transaction, PurchaseError> ;
      pub fn split_revenue(tx: &Transaction)
                        -> Result<RevenueSplit, SplitError> ;
      ```
    invariants :
      ‼ listing-price-flat (no-chance-mechanic) — runtime-asserted
      ‼ revenue-split sums-to 100% (assertion + property-test)
      ‼ Σ-mask-transferred at-tx (consent-on-transfer)
      ‼ attestation-emitted at-each-tx (§11)
      ‼ creator-signature-verified before-listing-published
    failure-modes :
      stripe-failure → tx aborted ; no-content-transfer ; rollback
      signature-fail → listing-rejected at-publish-time
      Σ-violation    → tx blocked (creator-revoked-mask after-list)

  § CSSL-PROVENANCE  (new-crate, Phase-K)
    location : compiler-rs/crates/cssl-provenance/
    target-LOC : ~2.5K + ~80-tests
    deps : cssl-audit-chain (D131 BLAKE3+Ed25519) +
           cssl-hdc (HDC-content-id) +
           cssl-substrate (Σ-mask)
    public-API-shape :
      ```rust
      pub struct ContentProvenance {
        content_id        : ContentId,           // BLAKE3
        hdc_content_id    : HdcContentId,        // 10000-D HDC fingerprint
        author_id         : CreatorId,
        author_signature  : Ed25519Signature,
        ancestors         : Vec<ContentId>,      // derivative-graph
        royalty_shares    : Vec<(CreatorId, BasisPoints)>, // 10000bp = 100%
        ai_collaborators  : Vec<CompanionAiAttribution>,
        merkle_proof      : MerkleProof,         // proof-in-daily-CT-log
        created_at        : OmegaTimestamp,
        sigma_mask_origin : SigmaMaskPacked,     // creator-set initial-mask
      }
      pub fn record_authorship(creator: &Creator, content: &Content)
                            -> Result<ContentProvenance, ProvError> ;
      pub fn derive_with_royalty(creator: &Creator, parent_ids: &[ContentId],
                                 derivation: &Content)
                              -> Result<ContentProvenance, ProvError> ;
      pub fn verify_provenance(prov: &ContentProvenance)
                            -> Result<Verification, VerifyError> ;
      pub fn daily_merkle_commit(records: &[ContentProvenance])
                              -> Result<MerkleRoot, CommitError> ;
      ```
    daily-merkle-protocol :
      every-24h-UTC platform aggregates new-provenance-records
      computes Merkle-root (BLAKE3-tree)
      publishes-root to public-CT-log + Twitter/Mastodon-public-post +
                      git-commit to public-repo (multi-anchor)
      individual-records can-prove-membership via-Merkle-proof
      ⇒ public-verifiable-without-our-database ; CT-style-anchoring
    NOT-blockchain-distinction :
      ¬ on-chain-tx + ¬ gas + ¬ token + ¬ smart-contract
      ≡ daily-batched-commit to public-pre-existing-channels
      ≡ inspired-by Certificate-Transparency (RFC-9162) + Sigstore Rekor
      ≡ provides "I-authored-X" public-verifiable-claim WITHOUT speculation-asset
    failure-modes :
      Merkle-commit-failure → retry next-cycle ; records buffered ;
                              SLA-spec : 99.9% commits within-25h-window
      provenance-fork (two-claims) → first-record-wins (timestamp + signature) ;
                                     dispute-process @ §6.LEGAL

  § CSSL-STRIPE-CONNECT  (new-crate, Phase-K)
    location : compiler-rs/crates/cssl-stripe-connect/
    target-LOC : ~1.5K + ~50-tests
    deps : stripe-rust-sdk (vendored or-via-async-stripe-crate)
    rationale-for-Stripe-Connect-Platform :
      Stripe-Connect is-the-payment-processor-of-record :
      ⟨A⟩ creator-onboarding (Express-account) handles KYC + identity-verification
      ⟨B⟩ money-transmitter-license (MTL) — Stripe-licensed in-all-50-US-states
      ⟨C⟩ EU + UK PSD2 + SCA + payment-services-directive — Stripe-handles
      ⟨D⟩ AML / sanctions-screening — Stripe-handles
      ⟨E⟩ sales-tax-facilitator — Stripe-Tax handles 45-US-states + EU OSS/IOSS
      ⟨F⟩ 1099-K issuance — Stripe-handles for-creator-tax-reporting
      ⟨G⟩ chargeback / dispute — Stripe-handles refund + clawback
      ⇒ massive-de-risk : platform-NEVER-touches PCI-data + NEVER-licensed-as-MSB
    public-API-shape :
      ```rust
      pub fn onboard_creator(creator: &Creator)
                          -> Result<StripeConnectAccount, OnboardError> ;
      pub fn create_charge(buyer: &Buyer, amount: Money,
                           split: RevenueSplit)
                        -> Result<StripeCharge, ChargeError> ;
      pub fn payout_status(account: &StripeConnectAccount)
                        -> Result<PayoutStatus, PayoutError> ;
      pub fn issue_1099k(creator: &Creator, year: u16)
                      -> Result<Form1099K, ReportingError> ;
      ```
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : exact-Stripe-product-mix (Connect-Express vs Connect-Custom)?
                  Apocky + counsel-review (Custom = more-control + more-burden)
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : alternative-processor (Adyen / Braintree) for-redundancy?
                  Apocky-decision-pending (single-processor risk vs complexity)

