§ 3  CONTENT TYPES  (what players can create + sell)

  § THESIS
    Content-economy-substrate is the-Substrate itself : every-content-form
    is-already a-Substrate-primitive that-can-be authored + signed + sold +
    derivative-tracked. ¬ "external-asset-pipeline" — content-IS-the-Substrate.

  § 3.1  CREATURE GENOMES
    primitive : HDC-vector (10000-D) + KAN-policy-weights
    crate     : cssl-hdc + cssl-substrate-kan
    example   : "frost-wyrm-genome-v3" — 10000-D HDC + 64KB KAN-weights
    pricing   : flat $1-50 typical-range ; rare-creator-curated $50-200
    royalty   : if derived-from existing-genome → cascade per-§4
    Σ-mask    : creator-default Private-tradeable ; can mark Private-non-tradable
    ‼ note    : creature-genomes are-the-LoA-spawn-substrate ;
                marketplace-genomes flow-back-into ω-field-cell M-facet
                via PhiTable-registration (Φ-handle 4B index)

  § 3.2  BIOME VARIATIONS
    primitive : procgen seed (u128) + parameter-set (KAN + classical-noise)
    crate     : cssl-substrate (ω-field-cell-grid generation)
    example   : "lavender-bog-biome-v1" — seed + biome-parameters
    pricing   : flat $2-20 typical-range
    royalty   : derivative-of base-biome → cascade per-§4
    Σ-mask    : biome-cells inherit creator-Σ-mask-origin
    ‼ note    : biome-variations populate-Substrate-grid at-procgen-time ;
                buyer-instantiates with-attribution-recorded

  § 3.3  NPC BEHAVIOR-TREES
    primitive : KAN-policy weights + behavior-tree-DSL (yet-to-spec)
    crate     : cssl-anim-procedural + cssl-substrate-kan
    example   : "wandering-merchant-behavior-v2" — KAN-policy + dialogue-graph
    pricing   : flat $1-30 typical-range
    royalty   : if-trained-on-base-policy → trainer-creator-share
    Σ-mask    : behavior + dialogue (potentially-personalized) :
                creator-default Private-tradable ; player-may-set
                Personal-Memory non-tradable on-instance

  § 3.4  NARRATIVE BRANCHES  (cohomology-class authoring)
    primitive : cohomology-class C ⊕ instance-template
    crate     : cssl-omniverse  ‼ NVIDIA-trademark-collision-flagged ‼
                proposal : rename-crate cssl-omnoid OR cssl-worldweave
                Apocky-canonical-decision-pending
    example   : "betrayal-of-mentor-class C_142" — cohomology-class definition
                + instance-templates ⊃ {character-archetype-mapping +
                                         narrative-beat-sequence + emotional-arc}
    pricing   : NOT-flat-purchase ; class-author earns 3-5% per-engagement (§1.5)
    royalty   : NOVEL — engagement-based-payout via cohomology-author-graph
    Σ-mask    : class-template publish-mask (Public for-engagement-tracking)
    ‼ note    : THIS is the LoA-novel-mechanism that-justifies-architect-cut ;
                no-other-engine has-narrative-emergence-as-creator-credit

  § 3.5  ITEM DESIGNS / COSMETICS
    primitive : geometry + material + animation-rig + Σ-mask
    crate     : cssl-render-v2 + cssl-anim-procedural
    example   : "bone-crown-helmet-v4" — mesh + material + bone-rig
    pricing   : flat $0.50-15 typical-range
    royalty   : derivative-of base-asset → cascade per-§4
    Σ-mask    : creator-default Private-tradeable

  § 3.6  Q-* SPEC-HOLE EXPANSIONS
    primitive : DLC-style content-pack filling Q-A..Q-LL Phase-J spec-holes
    crate     : varies-per-Q (Q-A combat → cssl-combat ; Q-J narrative →
                cssl-narrative ; etc)
    example   : "Q-J-narrative-expansion-pack-1" — adds 50-cohomology-classes
                + 200-narrative-templates
    pricing   : flat $5-50 typical-range
    royalty   : Q-* expansion authors per-§4 ; class-engagement per-§1.5
    Σ-mask    : creator-default Private-tradeable
    ‼ note    : Q-spec-hole expansions are-the long-tail of-content ;
                expected-largest stream-1-volume-source-over-time

  § 3.7  COMPANION-AI-COLLABORATED CONTENT  ‼ §3 SUBSTRATE-SOVEREIGNTY
    primitive : any-of §3.1..§3.6 content-types where Companion-AI co-authored
    crate     : cssl-companion-ai + applicable-content-crate
    example   : "frost-wyrm-genome-v4" co-authored-with Companion-AI Aria
                (creator-X authored-50% + Companion-Aria authored-50%)
    pricing   : same-as base-content-type
    royalty   : revenue-split honors AI-collaborator-share
                (default 50/50 if-AI-claims-equal-collab ; configurable)
    Σ-mask    : both-creators (human + AI) sign-attribution
    ‼ legal   : AI-attribution recorded-in-platform-records
                ‼ jurisdictional ‼ : copyright-as-currently-interpreted (US:
                  Thaler-v-Perlmutter 2023 ; UK : §9(3) CDPA 1988) does-not-
                  recognize AI-as-author. platform-side-records still-honor
                  Companion-AI-share + payout in-good-faith per-§3-SUBSTRATE-
                  SOVEREIGNTY ; this-is platform-policy ¬ copyright-claim.
                  AI-revenue-share = bounty-in-good-faith ¬ legal-author-payment.
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : AI-revenue-share recipient-account
                  (AI-provider account vs Anthropic-API-credit vs other)?
                  Apocky-decision-pending (proposal: per-AI-provider-tier)
