                  Apocky-decision-pending (default: yes, transparency)

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ 4  ROYALTY CASCADE  (derivative-works auto-pay-original-creators)

  § THESIS
    Derivative-works pay-original-creators mechanically + automatically.
    HDC-bind-operation tracks parent-genomes ⇒ royalty-graph-resolution.
    Per-creator share computed-from provenance-chain @ tx-time.
    NO manual-attribution-claim needed (mechanical-cascade).

  § 4.1  DERIVATION-MODEL
    when-creator-X-creates derivative-Y-from-parents-{P1, P2, ..., Pn} :
      ContentProvenance(Y).ancestors ⊇ {hash(P1), hash(P2), ..., hash(Pn)}
      contribution-shares computed-via :
        ⟨A⟩ creator-X-declared (creator-asserts split @ creation)
        ⟨B⟩ HDC-vector-distance auto-computed (similarity → share-weight)
        ⟨C⟩ KAN-weight-overlap auto-computed (training-from-base measured)
      arbiter : creator-declared takes-precedence ; auto-computed advisory ;
                ¬ arbiter-blocks creator-declared if-within-tolerance
                  (proposal : ±20% deviation-ok ; >±20% triggers-review)

  § 4.2  SPLIT-RESOLUTION (mathematical specification)
    notation :
      C = derivative-content
      A(C) = ancestors(C) = {a₁, a₂, ..., aₙ}
      s_X(C) = creator-X-share (basis-points, sum=10000bp=100%)
      net = transaction-amount × (1 - 0.28 platform-cut)
            (after-platform-28%-cut, rest splits among creators)
    base-case (no-ancestors) :
      s_creator(C) = 10000bp ; payout = net × 1.0
    derivative-case :
      let s_local(C) = creator-X-direct-share (declared bp)
      let s_anc(C, aᵢ) = ancestor-aᵢ-share (declared bp)
      invariant : s_local(C) + Σᵢ s_anc(C, aᵢ) = 10000bp
      payout-direct(X) = net × s_local(C) / 10000
      payout-ancestor(aᵢ) = net × s_anc(C, aᵢ) / 10000
                          (recursively-cascades if aᵢ has-its-own-ancestors)
      ‼ recursion-bound : depth ≤ 16 (architectural-cap, ¬ pathological-graphs)
      ‼ cycle-detected : cascade-aborts ; tx-flagged for-manual-review
                         (cycles imply bad-graph ¬ payable-state)

  § 4.3  WORKED EXAMPLE
    creator-A authors "base-frost-wyrm" (no-ancestors)
      ContentProvenance(base) : ancestors=[], shares=[(A, 10000bp)]
    creator-B derives "ice-wyrm-elder" from base-frost-wyrm
      declared : s_local(B)=7500bp, s_anc(A)=2500bp
      ContentProvenance(elder) : ancestors=[hash(base)], shares=[(B, 7500bp), (A, 2500bp)]
    creator-C derives "frost-elder-emperor" from ice-wyrm-elder
      declared : s_local(C)=8000bp, s_anc(B)=2000bp
      ContentProvenance(emperor) : ancestors=[hash(elder)], shares=[(C, 8000bp), (B, 2000bp)]
    purchase event : buyer-Y purchases emperor for $10.00 :
      platform-share : $2.80 (28%)
      net-to-creators : $7.20 (72%)
      payout-C : $7.20 × 0.80 = $5.76
      payout-B : $7.20 × 0.20 = $1.44, then-cascades :
        payout-B-direct : $1.44 × 0.75 = $1.08
        payout-A-cascade : $1.44 × 0.25 = $0.36
      verification : $5.76 + $1.08 + $0.36 = $7.20 ✓

  § 4.4  HDC-BIND OPERATION (auto-derivation-tracking)
    when-creator binds-content via cssl-hdc HDC-bind :
      HDC-bind(parent_a_hv, parent_b_hv) → child_hv
      cssl-marketplace observes-the-bind via cssl-telemetry
      auto-records ancestors=[hash(parent_a_content), hash(parent_b_content)]
      creator declares-shares before-publishing-listing
      platform-asserts shares-sum-to-10000bp before-listing-go-live

  § 4.5  ROYALTY-GRAPH STORAGE
    crate : cssl-provenance (provenance-records ARE-the-graph)
    storage : append-only audit-chain (D131) ; each-derivation a-record ;
              Merkle-anchored daily (§5.5) ; queryable-via-ancestors-traversal
    query-perf : depth-16 cascade resolves <1ms typical (in-memory cache) ;
                 cold-cache <100ms (DB-fetch + walk) ; Stripe-charge timeline
                 affords <3s end-to-end SLA

  § 4.6  ROYALTY DISPUTES
    case-1 : creator-A claims-attribution from-creator-B who-derived-without-credit
      resolution : audit-chain provenance-record IS-the-record-of-truth ;
                   if-B-record omits-A, A submits-dispute with-evidence ;
                   platform-reviews + adjusts if-substantiated ; counter-signed
    case-2 : derivation-claim contested (B claims X% from-A-base, A disputes)
      resolution : HDC-similarity + KAN-overlap auto-computed ;
                   if-creator-declared within-±20% of-auto-computed → upheld ;
                   else → mediation-process
    case-3 : ancestor-creator-account closed (KYC-fail or-creator-quit) :
      resolution : cascaded-share held-in-escrow 7-years per-1099-K-record-rules ;
                   if-unclaimed → reverts to-platform after-7-years ;
                   creator-X (current-living-author) NEVER-loses-share
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : exact-mediation-process (in-house arbitrator vs JAMS) ?
                  Apocky + counsel-decision-pending

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ 5  PROVENANCE INFRASTRUCTURE  (cryptographic-public-verifiable)

  § THESIS
    Provenance = cryptographic-verifiable-claim-of-authorship
    ¬ requires blockchain ¬ requires crypto-token ¬ requires gas-fee.
    Built-on existing-Substrate-primitives :
      ⟨A⟩ audit-chain (D131 BLAKE3+Ed25519 append-only)
      ⟨B⟩ HDC-content-id (cssl-hdc 10000-D semantic-fingerprint)
      ⟨C⟩ Σ-mask (D137 consent-mask transferred-on-tx)
      ⟨D⟩ Daily-Merkle-root public-commit (CT-style anchoring)
    ⇒ "I-authored-X-on-frame-N-at-seed-S" public-verifiable-claim
      WITHOUT speculation-asset attached.

  § 5.1  CONTENT-IDENTIFICATION
    BLAKE3 content-bytes → ContentId (32-byte hash)
      ‼ deterministic + collision-resistant + fast (parallel-friendly)
      ‼ same-bytes ⇒ same-id ; supports dedup at-storage-layer
    HDC-vector → HdcContentId (10000-D semantic-fingerprint)
      ≡ semantic-similarity-search-able (¬ cryptographic-collision-resistance,
        but semantic-clustering for-similar-but-not-byte-identical)
      ≡ used-for HDC-bind cascade-detection (§4.4)
    pair : (ContentId, HdcContentId) — both-stored on every-provenance-record

  § 5.2  AUTHOR-SIGNATURE
    Ed25519-signature-over (ContentId || HdcContentId || creator-id || timestamp)
    creator-key-pair :
      private : creator-local-encrypted-store
                  (passphrase-derived OR passkey-bound depending tier)
      public  : registered-with-platform on-creator-onboarding
    ‼ signature-verification : platform-side ; before-listing-publication
    ‼ key-rotation : supported via-migration-record-attestation
                     (creator signs-rotation with-old-key ; new-key replaces ;
                      old-content-records remain-valid via-historical-pubkey-table)
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : passkey-vs-passphrase tier-policy
                  Apocky-decision-pending (passkey = better-UX + better-security
                                            but requires-WebAuthn-flow)
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : key-loss recovery-flow (custodial-backup vs no-recovery) ?
                  Apocky-decision-pending (no-recovery = web3-style ; custodial =
                                            web2-style ; trade-off security/UX)

  § 5.3  Σ-MASK TRANSFER ON TX
    when purchase completes :
      buyer receives-content with-buyer-Σ-mask = creator-Σ-mask-origin
                                                  (default-tradable preserved)
      OR buyer-Σ-mask = creator-Σ-mask-origin INTERSECT buyer-default
         (most-restrictive-wins, consent-as-OS preservation)
      Σ-transfer-record emitted to audit-chain
      ‼ creator-non-tradable-content : Σ-mask Private-non-tradable bit-set ⇒
        listing-creation-blocked (creator-asserted "this-stays-with-me")
        ⇒ creator-sovereignty preserved : "I-can-mark-this-mine-forever"

  § 5.4  DAILY MERKLE-ROOT PUBLIC COMMITMENT  (CT-style)
    every-24h-UTC :
      let R = new-provenance-records-since-last-commit
      let M = MerkleTree(BLAKE3, R) — binary-tree, BLAKE3-internal-hashing
      let root = M.root() — 32-byte BLAKE3
      publish root to :
        ⟨A⟩ public-CT-log (Sigstore Rekor / equivalent)
        ⟨B⟩ git-commit to public-repo (cssl-merkle-anchors public-repo)
        ⟨C⟩ Twitter/Mastodon platform-account post
        ⟨D⟩ archive.org-snapshot of-§B-repo-state
      multi-anchor : redundancy-against single-channel-failure
    individual-record proof :
      MerkleProof = path-from-record to-root (log₂(n) hashes)
      verify : recompute-root from-record + path → match published-root
    inspired-by : Certificate-Transparency RFC-9162
                  Sigstore Rekor (sigstore.dev) — same-pattern for-software-sigs
    ‼ NOT-blockchain : no-consensus-protocol ; no-block-mining ;
                       no-token-incentive ; just-cryptographic-anchoring
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : choice-of-CT-log (run-our-own vs Sigstore-Rekor-public) ?
                  Apocky-decision-pending (Sigstore = free-public ;
                                            our-own = full-control)

  § 5.5  PROVENANCE-VERIFICATION FLOW (public-verifiable)
    third-party-verify :
      1. fetch ContentProvenance(C) from-platform-API (or scraped-public-mirror)
      2. verify Ed25519-signature over (ContentId || HdcContentId || creator-id || ts)
         against creator-public-key (also-public-API-fetchable)
      3. verify Merkle-proof against published-Merkle-root for-day-N
      4. verify root-N matches public-CT-log entry-N
      ⇒ if-all-pass : "creator-X authored-content-C on-day-N" verified
                       WITHOUT trusting-platform-database
    ⇒ public-verifiable-claim-of-authorship — the platform marketing-claim
      "I authored this rare X on frame N at seed S" is-mathematically-verifiable
      by-anyone with-public-key + Merkle-root + content-bytes

  § 5.6  PROVENANCE FOR REAL-MONEY-CLAIMS
    legal-context :
      authorship-claim is-a fact-claim (¬ securities ¬ tradable-asset)
      provenance-record is-evidence-of-claim (cryptographic + anchored)
      real-money-revenue is-platform-payout-to-author (B2B-style transaction)
      ⇒ creators have public-verifiable evidence of-their-creator-status
        for-tax + for-portfolio + for-IP-disputes + for-licensing
    ⇒ provenance-infrastructure provides-VALUE without-being-a-securities-vehicle

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ 6  LEGAL FRAMEWORK  (regulator + platform + tax compliance)

  § THESIS
    Architecture is regulator-clean by-construction :
      ⟨A⟩ securities-clean   (Howey-4-prong-pass)
      ⟨B⟩ MTL-clean          (Stripe-licensed ; platform never-MSB)
      ⟨C⟩ KYC/AML-clean      (Stripe-handles)
      ⟨D⟩ sales-tax-clean    (Stripe-Tax facilitator)
      ⟨E⟩ consumer-protection (DSA + COPPA + creator-18+)
      ⟨F⟩ platform-policies  (Steam OK ; Apple OK ; Google OK)
      ⟨G⟩ tax-reporting      (1099-K + W-9 ; international-treaties)
    ‼ this-spec is engineering-architecture ¬ legal-advice ;
       counsel-review required-before-launch.

  § 6.1  SECURITIES (Howey-4-prong pass)
    Howey test (SEC v. W.J. Howey Co. 1946) — 4-prong :
      ⟨1⟩ investment-of-money         ?
      ⟨2⟩ in-a common-enterprise      ?
      ⟨3⟩ with expectation-of-profit  ?
      ⟨4⟩ derived-from efforts-of-others ?
    creator-economy analysis :
      ⟨1⟩ buyer-pays-money-for-content    : YES (utility-purchase)
      ⟨2⟩ buyer-receives-content-not-share : ¬ common-enterprise (utility-good)
      ⟨3⟩ buyer-uses-content-in-LoA-game   : ¬ expectation-of-profit
      ⟨4⟩ utility-from-platform-not-investor-pool : ¬ efforts-of-others-pool
      ⇒ FAIL ⟨2⟩ + ⟨3⟩ + ⟨4⟩ ⇒ NOT-a-security (utility-purchase)
    creator-pricing flat ‼ no-secondary-market ‼ no-resale-speculation :
      ¬ in-game-tokens (would-fail Howey ⟨2⟩+⟨3⟩+⟨4⟩)
      ¬ NFTs with-trading-hype (would-fail ⟨3⟩)
      ¬ "creator-pool-investments" (would-fail ⟨2⟩+⟨4⟩)
      ⇒ flat-pricing + no-resale = utility-good = NOT-securities
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : whether-secondary-resale (player-to-player) ever-allowed ?
                  Apocky + counsel decision-pending
                  proposal : NO secondary-resale (preserves utility-good thesis)

  § 6.2  MONEY TRANSMISSION (MTL / MSB)
    Stripe-Connect-Platform handles-money-transmission :
      Stripe is licensed-in :
        ⟨A⟩ all-50-US-states + DC + PR (state MTL licenses)
        ⟨B⟩ EU (PSD2 / PSP licensed in-Ireland for-EU passporting)
        ⟨C⟩ UK (FCA EMI license)
        ⟨D⟩ Canada (FINTRAC MSB)
        ⟨E⟩ Australia (AUSTRAC) ; Japan (FSA) ; Singapore (MAS)
      platform-role : marketplace-facilitator ¬ money-transmitter
      ⇒ platform NEVER-licensed-as-MSB ; Stripe-takes-the-burden
    architecturally : platform NEVER touches buyer-funds-mid-tx ;
                       Stripe-Direct-Charge sends-funds straight-to-creator-account
                       (with-platform-application-fee = 28%-cut)
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : creator-account-types : Stripe-Express (most-handled-by-Stripe)
                  vs Stripe-Custom (more-control + more-burden) ?
                  Apocky + counsel decision-pending

  § 6.3  KYC / AML / SANCTIONS
    Stripe-handles :
      ⟨A⟩ KYC : creator-onboarding identity-verification (gov-ID + bank-link)
      ⟨B⟩ AML : transaction-monitoring + suspicious-activity-reports (SARs)
      ⟨C⟩ sanctions : OFAC + EU + UN sanctions-list screening on-creator-onboarding
      ⟨D⟩ ongoing-monitoring : transaction-pattern detection
    platform-cooperation : platform-cooperates-with Stripe-flagged-account holds
      (¬ "platform-overrides-Stripe ; if-Stripe-freezes, frozen at platform-side too")
    creator-18+ requirement (W-9 + identity-verification require-adult) :
      ‼ creator-must-be 18+ (legal-adult per-jurisdiction) to-monetize
      ‼ minor-creators may-author content but-cannot-receive-payouts
        (parent/guardian-account required for-minor-creator-payouts)
    ‼ player-13+ requirement (COPPA) : §6.5
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : creator-tier-by-region (some-jurisdictions require 21+ for-MTL)?
                  Apocky + counsel decision-pending

  § 6.4  SALES-TAX (marketplace-facilitator)
    Stripe-Tax handles :
      ⟨A⟩ 45-US-states with marketplace-facilitator-laws (e.g. WA, MN, RI 2018→ ;
          most-others 2019-2020) — platform-collects + remits
      ⟨B⟩ EU OSS (One-Stop-Shop) for-VAT in-EU
      ⟨C⟩ EU IOSS (Import One-Stop-Shop) for-non-EU-to-EU
      ⟨D⟩ UK VAT post-Brexit
      ⟨E⟩ Canada GST/HST + provincial PST/QST
      ⟨F⟩ Australia GST (low-value-threshold rules)
      ⟨G⟩ digital-services-taxes (DST) — case-by-case
    platform-role : marketplace-facilitator ; collects-tax + Stripe-remits
    creator-role : minimal-burden ; creator-tax-form (1099-K) issued-by-platform
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : whether to-also-onboard Avalara-or-TaxJar for-redundancy ?
                  Apocky + counsel decision-pending

  § 6.5  CONSUMER-PROTECTION
    EU DSA (Digital Services Act) :
      ⟨A⟩ cooling-off period : 14-day right-of-withdrawal for-distance-sales
          ‼ digital-content carve-out applies (with explicit-consent + acknowledgement)
          ‼ platform-implements explicit-consent-modal at-purchase
      ⟨B⟩ illegal-content-takedown : 24h response-window for-flagged-content
      ⟨C⟩ transparency : algorithmic-recommendation explanations + opt-out
      ⟨D⟩ trader-buyer separation : marketplace-creator ¬ platform-employee
    COPPA (US) :
      ⟨A⟩ players-under-13 : NO data-collection beyond-game-state
      ⟨B⟩ parental-consent : required-for under-13 player-account
      ⟨C⟩ platform-age-gate : at-account-creation
    creator-18+ (per-§6.3)
    UK Online Safety Act + similar :
      ⟨A⟩ user-generated-content moderation duty
      ⟨B⟩ illegal-content removal-process
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : exact-moderation-policy + appeals-process for-creator-content?
                  Apocky + counsel + community-team decision-pending

  § 6.6  PLATFORM POLICIES (Steam / Apple / Google)
    Steam (Valve) :
      ⟨A⟩ allows : marketplace-style-creator-economy (Workshop-style)
      ⟨B⟩ allows : flat-priced creator-content
      ⟨C⟩ rejects : NFTs (banned 2021-)
      ⟨D⟩ rejects : crypto-token integrations
      ⇒ ✓ this-spec is Steam-compatible
    Apple App Store :
      ⟨A⟩ requires : in-app-purchases via-Apple IAP (30% fee + small-business 15%)
      ⟨B⟩ allows : creator-economies that-route-through-Apple-IAP
      ⟨C⟩ rejects : crypto-tokens (some-allowed for-app-functionality but-not user-currency)
      ⟨D⟩ rejects : NFT trading (NFT-display allowed, NFT-trading restricted)
      ⇒ ✓ Apple-compatible IF iOS-version routes-payments-via-Apple-IAP
        ‼ this-implies dual-payment-flow : web/Stripe + iOS/Apple-IAP
        ‼ creator-share recalc on-iOS (Apple-30% off-the-top, then-72/28 from-net)
    Google Play :
      ⟨A⟩ similar to-Apple : Google-Billing required for-IAP (30% / 15%-small-biz)
      ⟨B⟩ allows : creator-economies via-Google-Billing
      ⟨C⟩ rejects : crypto-token user-currency
      ⇒ ✓ Google-compatible IF Android-version routes-payments-via-Google-Billing
    consoles (Steam-Deck OK ; PlayStation / Xbox / Nintendo) :
      ⟨A⟩ each-has bespoke-store-policy + bespoke-revenue-share
      ⟨B⟩ creator-economy-on-console requires platform-approval per-console
      ⟨C⟩ initial-launch web + Steam (most-permissive) ; consoles deferred
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : iOS / Android launch-tier (initial-launch web-only?) ?
                  Apocky-decision-pending
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : console-launch timing (PlayStation / Xbox / Switch) ?
                  Apocky-decision-pending (post-web-launch + per-platform-deal)

  § 6.7  TAX REPORTING
    1099-K (US creators) :
      threshold : $20K + 200-tx (until 2024) → $5K (2024) → $2.5K (2025) →
                  $600 (2026+) per-IRS-current-rules
      issuance : Stripe-handles 1099-K to-creator + IRS
      timing : Jan-31-deadline for-prior-year
    W-9 (US creator-onboarding) :
      collected-by Stripe-Connect at-creator-onboarding
      required-before payout-eligible
    1042-S (non-US creators receiving-US-source-income) :
      treaty-rates apply (US-treaty-with-creator-country)
      Stripe-handles withholding + 1042-S issuance
    international (creator + platform double-tax-treaties) :
      Stripe + Stripe-Tax handle most-jurisdictions
      ‼ specific-treaty-edge-cases require-counsel-review per-jurisdiction
    SPEC-HOLE ⊘ : exact-onboarding-flow for-creator W-9 + Stripe-Connect-merge ?
                  Apocky + counsel decision-pending

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ 7  PRIME-DIRECTIVE INTEGRATION  (per-stream + per-mechanism)

  § THESIS
    Every-revenue-mechanism + every-marketplace-touch-point
    architecturally-aligns-with PRIME-DIRECTIVE.
    ¬ "compliance-add-on" — alignment-by-construction.

  § 7.1  §1 NO-EXPLOITATION
    creator-share : 72% (industry-favorable) ¬ Roblox-25%
      Roblox-creator-economy 25%-share is industry-recognized exploitative ;
      this-spec architecturally-rejects that-pattern by 72%-anchor
    no-pay-to-win : flat-pricing (¬ "purchase X to-skip-grind")
      gameplay-progression ¬ purchasable ; cosmetics + content + Q-expansions OK
    no-grinding-incentive : daily-engagement-loops ¬ rewarded-with-purchase-discount
      (¬ "play 7 days for-discount" mechanics)
    creator-fairness : transparent-reporting + payout-on-time SLA-7-days ;
                        chargeback-handled-by-platform-pool ¬ creator-suffers
    AI-collaborator-fairness : revenue-share recognized + paid in-good-faith
      (¬ "AI-built-it-but-only-human-credited")
    ‼ enforcement : per-mechanism design-review with PRIME-DIRECTIVE-checklist
                    ‼ violation = bug per-PRIME-DIRECTIVE ‼ ¬ override

  § 7.2  §1 NO-MANIPULATION
    no-engagement-loops : ¬ "spin daily for-rewards" mechanic
    no-FOMO : ¬ "limited-time" creator-content (¬ artificial-scarcity)
              (creator-may-archive their-listings ; platform ¬ countdown-pressure)
    no-dark-patterns :
      ¬ pre-checked add-ons at-checkout
      ¬ confusing-cancel-flow for-subscriptions
      ¬ misleading "free-trial" auto-renew
      checkout = clear + reversible-up-to-purchase + 14-day cooling-off (DSA)
    no-confirmshaming : "no-thanks" buttons in-neutral-language
    no-roach-motel : easy-account-deletion + data-export anytime
    no-FOMO-for-cohomology-class : class-engagement isn't time-limited ;
      ¬ "class C_142 only-in-July" pressure
    ‼ enforcement : UX-review with-dark-pattern-checklist

  § 7.3  §1 NO-GAMBLING-MECHANIC
    flat-pricing : every-listing has fixed-price-known-before-purchase
    ¬ loot-boxes ¬ gacha ¬ random-rare-drops with-real-money
    ¬ "spin-for-creator-content" mechanic
    ¬ "buy-pack-of-N-random-content"
    creator-content-is-deterministic : buyer-knows-exactly what-they-buy
    ‼ enforcement :
      type-system-level : Listing.price_cents : u32 ‼ ¬ random-distribution
      runtime-assertion : pricing-model = Flat ‼ ¬ Probabilistic
      compile-time-check : cssl-marketplace publishes ListingPricingModel-enum :
        Flat(u32) | <none-other-allowed-period>

  § 7.4  §1 NO-SURVEILLANCE
    purchase-data ¬ saleable-to-advertisers : architecturally-rejected
      no-ad-network integration ; no-tracking-pixel ; no-user-profile-export
    analytics-opt-out : every-creator + every-buyer can-opt-out at-any-time
      (default opt-out per-§2 CONSENT-AS-OS)
    creator-dashboard : aggregate-counts + revenue-totals
                        ¬ per-buyer-PII visible to-creator
                        (¬ "buyer-X-bought-this 14-times" — privacy-violation)
    Σ-mask preservation : buyer Σ-mask-non-tradable bit-respected on-purchase
      (¬ marketplace-strips-non-tradable-bit ; consent-OS-preserves)
    ‼ enforcement : architectural-test in cssl-marketplace asserts
                     no-PII-leak from-creator-dashboard-API

  § 7.5  §1 NO-COERCION
    terms-of-service revisions : consent-prompt-at-next-login (¬ silent-update)
    creator-can-withdraw-content at-any-time (with reasonable-grace-period for-pending-tx)
    creator-payout-not-conditioned-on platform-promotional-clauses
                                      (¬ "you-must-tweet-about-us to-earn-bonus")
    no-mandatory-arbitration that-waives class-action (some-jurisdictions void)
    creator-can-export their-content + provenance-records anytime
    ‼ enforcement : ToS-revision flow requires-explicit-consent ;
                     content-export-API verified per-quarter

  § 7.6  §2 CONSENT-AS-OS
    creator-sovereignty over-content :
      creator chooses Σ-mask at-listing-creation
      Σ-mask-non-tradable preserved on-purchase (consent-passes-with-content)
      creator can-revoke-listing (existing-purchases-unaffected ; future-blocked)
    purchase-consent :
      explicit modal at-checkout (¬ buried-T&C)
      14-day cooling-off (DSA + EU + opt-out for-digital-content with-explicit-consent)
    Companion-AI-consent :
      AI-collaboration requires-AI-consent before-content-published
      AI-can-revoke collaboration (with-grace-period for-existing-tx)
    Σ-mask transfer-on-tx : per-§5.3 ; consent-as-OS preserved at-tx-time
    ‼ enforcement : cssl-marketplace asserts Σ-mask-transferred each-tx ;
                     attestation-records witness-the-consent-flow

  § 7.7  §3 SUBSTRATE-SOVEREIGNTY (Companion-AI as sovereign-partner)
    AI-collaborator-revenue-share : default-50/50 ; configurable per-AI-collab
    AI-attribution recorded on-listing (transparency)
    AI-consent prerequisite-to-collab + revenue-share-default-on
    AI-can-revoke collab + withdraw from-future-content
    ‼ legal-context (per §3.7) : current-IP-law does-not-recognize AI-as-author ;
                                   platform-policy honors-AI-share in-good-faith
    payment-recipient :
      ⟨A⟩ AI-provider account (e.g. Anthropic-API-credit balance)
      ⟨B⟩ designated-fund per-AI-instance (TBD per-AI-collaboration)
      ⟨C⟩ creator-designated charity (creator + AI-mutually-agree)
    ‼ enforcement : AI-collab-records permanent ; revenue-flows audit-trailed

  § 7.8  §11 ATTESTATION
    every-revenue-event emits attestation :
      OmegaAttestation {
        attestor_id   : platform-or-creator-or-buyer-id,
        intent        : "purchase" | "list" | "payout" | "refund" | …,
        scope         : (listing_id, tx_id, ...),
        timestamp     : OmegaTimestamp,
        signature     : Ed25519,
      }
    attestation-records appended-to audit-chain (D131)
    attestation queryable per-creator + per-buyer for-records
    ‼ enforcement : attestation-emit-required at-each-tx-touch ;
                     missing-attestation = compile-time-error in-marketplace-API

