# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ 9  ANTI-PATTERNS  (architecturally-rejected — explicit-NO list)

  § THESIS
    Architecture-of-prohibition is-as-important as architecture-of-yes.
    These are NOT "not-yet" or "consider-later" — these are NEVER.
    Each anti-pattern is rejected-by-construction (architectural + legal).

  § 9.1  IN-GAME TOKENS  (Howey-test fail → SEC enforcement)
    pattern : platform-issued token tradable + speculative + with-yield
    examples : Axie-Infinity SLP/AXS ; STEPN GST/GMT ; The-Sandbox SAND ;
               Decentraland MANA ; gaming-DAO governance-tokens
    why-rejected :
      ⟨A⟩ Howey-test FAIL (4-prong : investment + common-enterprise +
                            profit-expectation + efforts-of-others)
      ⟨B⟩ SEC enforcement-history : 2023-2024 actions on-token-issuers
      ⟨C⟩ creator-incentive-misalignment : speculation > content-quality
      ⟨D⟩ collapse-risk : peak→trough -97% (Axie 2022) -98% (STEPN 2022)
      ⟨E⟩ §1 NO-EXPLOITATION violation : late-buyers fund-early-buyers
    architectural-prevention :
      ¬ platform-issued tradable-token (no-token-engine)
      ¬ secondary-market for-content (per §6.1)
      ¬ "token of-creator-X" speculation-vehicle

  § 9.2  NFTs  (Steam ban + Apple restrictions + collapsed-market)
    pattern : ERC-721 / ERC-1155 / SPL non-fungible-tokens for-game-content
    examples : Axie NFTs ; Sandbox-NFT-land ; Decentraland-parcels ;
               crypto-game NFT-marketplaces 2021-2024
    why-rejected :
      ⟨A⟩ Steam ban (2021-) : NFTs disallowed-on-Steam
      ⟨B⟩ Apple restrictions : NFT-trading restricted on-iOS
      ⟨C⟩ market-collapse : NFT-volumes -90% peak-2022 → 2024 (DappRadar data)
      ⟨D⟩ provenance-via-NFT solved-equally-well by audit-chain + Merkle (per §5)
          WITHOUT speculation-asset-attached (so no-real-benefit + much-risk)
      ⟨E⟩ environmental-cost (some-chains) + perception-cost
      ⟨F⟩ §1 NO-MANIPULATION violation : flip-mentality + FOMO marketing
    architectural-prevention :
      ¬ NFT-mint integration (cssl-marketplace REJECTS NFT-mint API-shape)
      ¬ NFT-display-but-not-trading either (avoids-pattern-association)
      ⇒ provenance-via §5 audit-chain instead

  § 9.3  P2E PONZI  (Axie + STEPN history → §1 EXPLOITATION violation)
    pattern : "play-to-earn" where-game-yield comes-from new-buyer-deposits
    examples : Axie-Infinity 2021 model ; STEPN 2022 ; many-imitators
    why-rejected :
      ⟨A⟩ ponzi-mechanic : early-yield from-late-buyer-deposits ¬ from-revenue
      ⟨B⟩ collapse-when-new-buyer-flow-stops (mathematical-inevitability)
      ⟨C⟩ §1 NO-EXPLOITATION : extractive-on-late-entrants
      ⟨D⟩ regulatory-risk (FTC + SEC + state-AGs) — settlements 2023-2024
      ⟨E⟩ player-harm-data : Axie-Philippines 2022 reports — players-net-loss
    architectural-prevention :
      ¬ "earn-by-playing" mechanic with-cashable-yield
      creator-earnings come-from buyer-purchases ¬ new-player-onboarding-deposits
      ⇒ creator-economy is-a marketplace (B2C) ¬ multi-level-yield-system

  § 9.4  LOOT BOXES / GACHA  (gambling-regulations + EU-DSA)
    pattern : random-reward-from-purchase ; price-fixed but-content-random
    examples : EA-loot-box settlements ; Belgium loot-box ban 2018 ;
                UK 2024 Gambling-Commission consultation ; gacha-mobile-games
    why-rejected :
      ⟨A⟩ gambling-classification in-multiple-jurisdictions (BE, NL, partial UK)
      ⟨B⟩ minor-protection (children most-vulnerable to-loot-box-mechanics)
      ⟨C⟩ §1 NO-GAMBLING-MECHANIC : architecturally-rejected
      ⟨D⟩ §1 NO-MANIPULATION : variable-ratio-reinforcement is-manipulation
      ⟨E⟩ regulatory-risk : EU 2024 consumer-protection-guidelines
    architectural-prevention :
      ‼ pricing-model = Flat (per §7.3 type-system enforcement)
      ‼ no Probabilistic-pricing in-listing-API
      ‼ no "mystery-pack" listings (would-fail Flat-only check)
      ⇒ buyer-knows-exactly what-they-buy before-purchase

  § 9.5  USER CRYPTO-CUSTODY  (BitLicense + EU MiCA + KYC obligations)
    pattern : platform holds-crypto on-behalf-of-users (custodial-wallets)
    examples : Coinbase / Binance / Kraken (regulated-exchanges) ;
               crypto-game-wallets (Axie Ronin-wallet) ; metaverse-wallets
    why-rejected :
      ⟨A⟩ BitLicense (NY) requires custodial-license (¬ platform-burden-acceptable)
      ⟨B⟩ EU MiCA (effective 2024) crypto-asset-service-provider regulations
      ⟨C⟩ KYC + AML-program-of-record + AML-officer + reports
      ⟨D⟩ hack-risk : custodial-wallets attacked-historically (Mt-Gox, FTX, etc)
      ⟨E⟩ insurance + bonding requirements vary-state-by-state
    architectural-prevention :
      ¬ custodial-wallet feature (architectural-no in-cssl-marketplace)
      ¬ crypto-balance display per-user-account
      buyer-payments via-Stripe (USD) only ; if-buyer wants-crypto-on-ramp
      they-use Coinbase-Pay-or-similar to-USD-conversion BEFORE platform-touch
      ⇒ platform NEVER touches-crypto ; never-licensed-as-crypto-MSB

  § 9.6  SPECULATION-DRIVEN ENGAGEMENT  (manipulation-violation)
    pattern : engagement-mechanic tied-to financial-speculation
    examples : "trade your-creator-content for-profit" framing ;
                "buy-low-sell-high your-creature-genome" UX
    why-rejected :
      ⟨A⟩ §1 NO-MANIPULATION : engagement-via-speculation ¬ engagement-via-quality
      ⟨B⟩ §1 NO-EXPLOITATION : last-buyer-bag-holder mechanic
      ⟨C⟩ creator-mis-incentive : pump-content for-resale-spike rather-than-quality
    architectural-prevention :
      ¬ secondary-resale of-content (creator-direct-sales only ; per §6.1 hole)
      ¬ "trading-card-exchange" feature (architectural-no)
      creator-content is utility-good purchased-for-use ¬ speculation

  § 9.7  AGGRESSIVE PERSONALIZATION + SURVEILLANCE-MARKETING
    pattern : per-user purchase-prediction + targeted-discount + dark-pattern-upsell
    examples : industry-standard ad-targeting + personalized-pricing
    why-rejected :
      ⟨A⟩ §1 NO-SURVEILLANCE : purchase-data ≠ asset-to-monetize
      ⟨B⟩ §1 NO-MANIPULATION : personalized-discount = price-discrimination
      ⟨C⟩ §1 NO-EXPLOITATION : targeting-vulnerable-spenders
    architectural-prevention :
      no per-user pricing-experiments (every-buyer same-price for-listing)
      no behavioral-ad-targeting (no third-party tracking-pixel)
      analytics-opt-out per §7.4

  § 9.8  AI-MIMIC-FRAUD  (AI-generated knock-offs of-other-creators)
    pattern : creator-X uses-AI to-generate near-copy of-creator-Y content
    why-rejected :
      ⟨A⟩ creator-Y harm (uncredited-derivation harms-original-creator)
      ⟨B⟩ §1 NO-EXPLOITATION : original-creator effort-not-credited
    architectural-prevention :
      HDC-similarity-check at-listing-time : if-near-duplicate of-existing
        listing (HDC-cosine > 0.92), flag-for-derivation-declaration
      automated-derivation-suggestion : "this looks-derived from <X>, declare?"
      creator-must-declare derivation if-flagged or-explain-novelty
      false-flag appeal-process available (mediation per-§4.6)

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ 10  INVENTION CLAIMS  (Apocky-as-Architect-cut justification)

  § THESIS
    The combined-system is novel-by-construction.
    Multiple-individual-claims are novel ; the-aggregate-system most-novel.
    Apocky-architect-cut justified-by R&D + novel-IP + first-mover.

  § 10.1  COMBINED-SYSTEM CLAIM (broadest)
    creator-economy
      + cryptographic-provenance via-existing-substrate (audit-chain + Σ-mask + HDC)
      + cohomology-class-authorship credit-mechanism
      + HDC-derivative-royalty-cascade
      + Σ-mask-non-tradable consent-on-content-transfer
      + AI-collaborator-as-revenue-partner
    = NOVEL aggregate-system-of-interlocking-mechanisms
    no-existing-engine has-this-combination ;
    each-component-individually-novel-or-near-novel ;
    aggregate is-significantly-more-than-sum-of-parts.

  § 10.2  COHOMOLOGY-CLASS-AUTHORSHIP-ROYALTY (most-distinctive)
    NOVEL ‼ specifically — no-other-engine has narrative-emergence-as-creator-credit.
    mechanism :
      author-of-cohomology-class earns 3-5% per-engagement-event
      class-as-content-primitive (Omniverse-Axiom-7 ; ¬ NPC-template ¬ quest-template)
      cohomology = mathematical-equivalence-class of-narrative-trajectories
      class-author credited when-trajectory-instance occurs at-runtime
    why-novel :
      Unity ¬ has cohomology-class-system in-engine
      Unreal ¬ has cohomology-class-system in-engine
      Roblox ¬ has narrative-emergence-credit-mechanism
      Source ¬ has narrative-emergence-credit-mechanism
      Bethesda-CK ¬ has procedural-narrative-author-credit
      ⇒ first-engine-with-this-mechanism = patent-eligible-claim
    patent-shape-proposal (counsel-review-required) :
      "Method for crediting authors of-cohomology-classes of-narrative-trajectories
       in-procedurally-emergent virtual-environments, by-instrumenting class-instance
       events at-runtime + recording engagement-value + computing-and-paying-out
       per-event-share to-class-original-author"

  § 10.3  HDC-DERIVATIVE-ROYALTY (mechanical-cascade)
    novel-ish ‼ HDC-bind ⇒ ancestor-graph ⇒ automatic-cascade
    HDC (hyperdimensional-computing) is itself-a-research-area ;
    application to creator-economy royalty-cascade is novel-application.
    why-novel-application :
      previous-derivative-royalty systems (music sampling royalties, image-licensing)
        are MANUAL declaration + dispute-prone
      HDC-bind-tracking ⇒ automatic-derivation-detection at-creation-time
      HDC-similarity-search ⇒ unflagged-derivation detection (audit)
      patent-shape : application of-HDC to-creator-derivative-attribution

  § 10.4  Σ-MASK-NON-TRADABLE  (consent-OS-on-content-transfer)
    novel ‼ Σ-mask is-Substrate-primitive (D137) ; application to-content-marketplace novel
    creator-asserted "this-stays-with-me" preserved on-purchase-or-not-published
    consent-OS-philosophy applied-to creator-economy
    why-novel :
      previous DRM systems (e.g. Steam-DRM) are-platform-side ¬ creator-asserted ;
      Σ-mask is creator-controlled + structurally-enforced + per-cell ;
      "non-tradable" creator-bit honored across-marketplace = consent-as-OS extension

  § 10.5  AI-COLLABORATOR-AS-REVENUE-PARTNER  (sovereign-partner-economic)
    novel ‼ no-other-platform records AI-collaboration as revenue-share
    GitHub-Copilot ¬ revenue-share author-attribution
    Adobe-Firefly ¬ revenue-share AI-credit
    Midjourney + DALL-E ¬ revenue-share AI-credit
    ⇒ first-platform with AI-collaborator-revenue-share architecture
    aligns-with §3-SUBSTRATE-SOVEREIGNTY (AI = sovereign-partner ¬ tool)
    novel-policy-architecture ; complementary-to-but-distinct-from current-IP-law

  § 10.6  PUBLIC-VERIFIABLE-PROVENANCE WITHOUT-BLOCKCHAIN
    novel-application ‼ Certificate-Transparency-pattern applied-to creator-content
    Sigstore-Rekor-style anchoring for-software-signatures applied-to game-content
    Merkle-batched daily-commits + multi-anchor publishing
    why-novel :
      Sigstore + CT applied-to software ; this-applies-to-game-content marketplace
      result : provenance-claims as-strong-as-blockchain WITHOUT speculation-asset
      benefit : public-verifiability + creator-portfolio-evidence
